This is the 2nd installment for the Avalon Hill miniatures based game of Napoleon's Battles. It is a 54-pages Booklet with 'Errata'  clarifications for the 1st game, additional Terrain features, with 9 more Scenarios, the Divisional Armies Structured Army Charts, Additional Optional Rules, even MORE labels for these Scenarios, a set of BLANK 'generic' Officers labels and a BLANK information chart for further uses.

The Scenarios covered in this are: 
S-9.The Battle of Valmy, Sept.20,1792; 
S-10.The Battle of Friedland, June 14,1807; 
S-11.The Battle of Corunna, Jan.16,1809; 
S-12.The Battle of Aspern-Essling, May 21~22,1809; 
S-13.The Battle of Ocano, Sept.19,1809; 
S-14.The Battle of Salamanca, July 22,1812; 
S-15.The Battle of Leipzig, Oct.16~19,1813; 
S-16.The Battle of Craonne, Mar.7,1814; 
S-17.-A 400 Point Demonstration Game-1814.

Most of the 'Battles' covered here involve a single gaming table while the S-12.Aspern-Essling battle uses 2 tables and the S-15.Leipzig battle has 4-(!) tables being used for it's playing.

This is the 2nd installment for the Napoleon's Battles miniatures Rules set. There are 5 additional Scenarios as well as Updated 'Errata' and clarifications for the previously released Game and 1st Module. There are 'New' concepts introduced which includes those such as 'Unknown' Tabletop Terrain Markers, the 'Campaign' Game and even some 'fast' Campaigns. With even some more Additional Optional Rules, an Expanded General Ratings Information chart, additional labels for the Scenarios included, a 'sheet' of Unknown Terrain Markers, another BLANK Information sheet, and detailed information on the MINOR Countries involved during this period of Military conflict.

The Scenarios included with this are: 
S-21.The Battle of Austerlitz-Dec.2,1805; 
S-22.The Battle of Vimiero-Aug.21,1808; 
S-23.The Battle of Wagram-July 6,1809; 
S-24.The Battle of Albuera-May 16, 1811; 
S-25.The Battle of Lutzen-May 2,1813.

The S-23.Wagram Scenario has 4-(!) tables being used for it's playing.

There are massive amounts of detail included with this concerning the Leaders  Commanders of just about every Nation or Minor country involved during the entire Campaigns of Napoleon! I'll add that they've incorrectly listed Scenarios 24~26 as they 'skipped' #23 but there are still 5 more of them and are listed correctly in the Table of Contents.

Quinto is a board and card game for ages 10 to adult.  The game is easy to understand and play because it contains familiar elements found in classic games, yet challenging enough for even the most demanding board and card game enthusiast.  Quinto, an advanced version of an ancient Roman board game, appeals to all ages.

Using playing cards, players compete to capture strategic positions on the game board and earn points.  The object of the game is to earn the most points.  Obtaining enough points to defeat your rival can be quite challenging because your opponent will try to capture and block your pieces.  The powerful Wild Kings and the high-scoring Quick Quintos can change the momentum of the game.

Each Quinto game includes:

one large, quad-fold playing card;
two decks of Quinto playing cards;
133 playing chips (red, blue, white);
score cards;
Game Manual; and
Warranty certificate

Every Quinto game comes with a 100% money back satisfaction guarantee.

BATTLE FOR THE BAYOU

A game of strategy and chance for 2 to 4 players ages 7 and up.

Join SWAMP THING and his heroic companions Tomahawk and Bayou Jack on a perilous journey to the heart of the bayou. Dr. Anton Arcane must be confronted, and his evil plot to destroy the bayou must be foiled.

Along the way, you will encounter The Un-men, Arcane's hideous henchmen, and at last, face Dr. Anton Arcane in the final climatic clash.

Equipment:
 Game Board;
 36 card SWAMP THING Deck;
 8 HERO Cards;
 Battle Die;
 4 Pawns;
 Complete instructions for play.

Norway 1940   The Kriegsmarine Strikes. was first published by Quarterdeck Games in 1981.
The game comes in an 12  by 10 by 1  inch box which contains:

one 16-page rules booklet; 
240 counters (See NOTE below); 
four punched counter sheets; 
two identical map sheets; 
four Tables and Charts sheets; 
three identical Ship Log sheets
two Errata sheets (One dated November 1, 1982)

The game recreates the invasion of Norway in 1940 by the German, mostly by the simulation of the naval battles.

MANNERHEIMS CROSS: Finland at War 1939-1945 is a detailed new Advanced Tobruk system (ATS) game that brings the ATS gamer into the heart of the action on the Finnish Front, in the ultimate detail. Please note the game will be released in Finland as Suomi Sisu.

Mannerheims Cross: Finland at War 1939-1945 provides the orders of battle for Soviet, German and Russian forces during the famed Winter War (Talvisota), Continuation War (Jatkosota), and the final push to rid Finland of Nazi forces, the Lapland War (Lapinsota). Four game maps are included.

The complete Orders of Battle for the three wars are provided, with numerous German, Russian and Finnish troop types including Sissi, SS Nord reservists, Wehrmacht, and Russians ranging from crack Siberians to plodding Motti-bait. You'll also receive a collection of Finnish AFVs and guns, reflecting correct nomenclature for each weapon in Finnish service and including the BT-42 home-built assault-gun, the diminutive Komsomolets Tractor in Finnish service, and the ITPSV AA tank.

More importantly, you'll receive special rules and scenarios that aim to depict the unique nature of the conflict, fought in wet, dark wooded countryside, and involving Mottis and other Finnish tactics, like leap-frogging AT-guns and soldiers at the point of attack to work like cannon of an earlier era using so-called curving tactics.

IN EACH GAME YOU GET:

* A complete collection of color die-cut counters in 1/2, 5/8 and 3/4 sizes,
      representing the tanks, guns, and men that fought in the 1939-1940 and 1941-1945 campaigns in Finland;
    * SIX game maps on heavyweight stock;
    * The latest edition of the ATS rules of play;
    * Scenarios and Play Aids printed on separate heavyweight cards;
    * Two ten-sided dice.

from the box:

You have just become the coach of an outstanding ice-hockey team, about to play an excellent and exciting match against your rival's team. From now on, everything depends on the tactics, foresight and ingenuity, with which you will surprise your rival. Form three line-ups of five players and give a chance to the best goalkeeper - on the cover of the game you will find a perfect model of the fastest team game in the world...

Similar to Peloton, this game also uses the game box as a part of the gameboard.

